text.section:
The administrative regulations shall include:
A process for an individual who believes that a factual error or errors have been found to file notice of his or her findings;
A methodology for validating the accuracy of a claim of factual error;
The development of conditions to include in publishers' contracts specifying protocols for correcting errors which take into account the following:
The extensiveness of the errors found;
The remaining time left until the next textbook adoption cycle at the time the claim is determined to be valid;
Conditions that would necessitate replacement of a book in its entirety; and
Conditions that could be addressed through the insertion of corrections in textbooks without replacement;
Notice to school districts of errors, if found, and the resolution determined to be available; and
Notice to the claimant relative to the validation review and the resolution determined to be available if the claim of error was validated.
